# Project Overview
This is a CRM application (dvr-crm) built with TanStack Start, Better Auth, and Drizzle ORM on PostgreSQL.
- Package manager: pnpm
- Runtime: Node.js, Vite + Nitro
- Language: TypeScript (strict)
- UI: shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS v4
- Validation: Zod v4
- Client state: Zustand
- Forms: TanStack Form
- Tables: TanStack Table

# Directory Structure
- `src/routes/`        — File-based routes (TanStack Router/Start)
- `src/db/schema.ts`   — Single Drizzle schema file (all tables + relations)
- `src/db/index.ts`    — Drizzle db instance (`export const db`)
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui components
- `src/components/`    — App-level components (forms, tables, etc.)
- `src/stores/`        — Zustand stores (client-only state)
- `src/lib/utils.ts`   — Shared utilities (`cn`, etc.)
- `utils/auth.ts`      — Better Auth server instance
- `utils/auth-client.ts` — Better Auth client instance (`authClient`)
- `utils/middleware.ts`  — TanStack Start middleware (auth guard)
- `utils/permissions.ts` — RBAC access control (`ac`, `admin`, `manager`, `user` roles)
- `auth-schema.ts`     — Better Auth base schema (do not edit manually)
- `drizzle.config.ts`  — Drizzle Kit config (schema at `src/db/schema.ts`, dialect: postgresql)

# Import Aliases
- `@/` maps to `src/` — use for all src imports
- `utils/` — use bare (no alias) for auth/middleware/permissions imports
- Never use relative `../` imports when an alias is available

# TanStack Start Rules
- ALWAYS use `createServerFn` for any server-side data access (DB queries, auth checks)
- ALWAYS load initial data via `loader` in `createFileRoute`, never in `useEffect`
- ALWAYS read loader data with `Route.useLoaderData()` — never prop-drill it
- Use `router.invalidate()` after mutations to refresh loader data
- Use `router.navigate()` or `router.history.back()` for post-action navigation
- Never fetch data on the client with `useEffect` + `fetch` — use loaders or server functions
- Middleware lives in `utils/middleware.ts`; auth guard is already applied globally
- For server functions that need the current session/request, use `getRequest()` from `@tanstack/react-start/server` and pass headers to `auth.api.*`
- Route file naming convention:
  - `entity.tsx`             — list view with `<Outlet />`
  - `entity.new.tsx`         — create dialog (renders over list)
  - `entity.$id.update.tsx`  — edit dialog
  - `entity.$id.delete.tsx`  — confirm-delete dialog/alert
  - `entity_.$id.view.tsx`   — detail view (underscore = non-nested layout)
- Dialog/modal routes open over the parent list route — always `open` prop is hardcoded to `true`, close via `router.navigate` or `router.history.back()`
- Avoid `useEffect`, `useMemo`, `useCallback` unless absolutely necessary — prefer derived values and loaders

# Drizzle ORM Rules
- All schema lives in `src/db/schema.ts` — one file, append new tables there
- Always define relations with `relations()` alongside the table definition
- DB instance is `import { db } from '@/db'`
- Prefer `db.query.<table>.findMany/findFirst` with `with:` for relational queries
- Use `eq`, `and`, `or`, `inArray`, `isNull`, `isNotNull` etc. from `drizzle-orm`
- Use `db.insert().values().returning()` for inserts that need the result
- Use `db.update().set().where().returning()` for updates
- Use `db.delete().where()` for deletes
- Use `db.transaction()` for multi-step operations
- Column conventions:
  - Primary keys: `text('id').primaryKey()` (string UUIDs or cuid2)
  - Timestamps: `timestamp('created_at').defaultNow().notNull()`
  - Updated at: `timestamp('updated_at').$onUpdate(() => new Date()).notNull()`
  - Foreign keys: always add `{ onDelete: 'cascade' }` unless intentionally restricted
  - Add `index()` on foreign key columns used in frequent queries
- After schema changes run: `pnpm db:generate` then `pnpm db:migrate`
- Never use `pnpm db:push` in production — only during development
- Schema changes that affect Better Auth tables must be synced with `auth-schema.ts`

# Better Auth Rules
- Server auth instance: `import { auth } from 'utils/auth'`
- Client auth instance: `import { authClient } from 'utils/auth-client'`
- Auth API calls on the server always require `headers: request.headers` — get request with `getRequest()` from `@tanstack/react-start/server`
- RBAC roles are: `admin`, `manager`, `user` — defined in `utils/permissions.ts`
- Permission statements: `company` (create/update/delete), `task` (create/update/delete/assign/unassign)
- To check permissions server-side use `auth.api.userHasPermission()`
- To call admin actions client-side use `authClient.admin.*`
- Auth route handler is at `src/routes/api/auth/$.ts` — do not modify it
- `tanstackStartCookies()` plugin is already configured — cookies are handled automatically
- Social provider (Google) and email/password are both enabled

# shadcn/ui Rules
- Install new components with: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- All UI components are in `src/components/ui/`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Use `<ResponsiveDialog>` from `@/components/ui/responsive-dialog` for modal routes
- Use `<AlertDialog>` for destructive confirm actions (ban, delete)
- Use `sonner` (`toast`) for success/error notifications after mutations
- Tailwind CSS v4 — no `tailwind.config.js`, configuration is in CSS via `@theme`

# General Code Rules
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, always infer types from Drizzle schema or Zod
- Derive Zod schemas from Drizzle tables using `drizzle-zod` when validating forms
- One route component per file — `function RouteComponent()` (not exported, not named after the route)
- Server functions defined at the top of the route file, before `createFileRoute`
- `inputValidator` is required on server functions that accept parameters
- Always handle loading/error states in forms (disable buttons, show toasts)
- Do not use `next-themes` ThemeProvider patterns — check `__root.tsx` for existing theme setup


# Component Extraction Rules
- Route files (`src/routes/`) are ONLY for routing concerns:
  - `createFileRoute` config (loader, search params, error boundary)
  - `createServerFn` definitions that belong to this route
  - The `RouteComponent` function (thin shell — layout + data passing only)
- Route files must NOT contain:
  - Large JSX trees (more than ~60 lines in the component body)
  - Inline form implementations
  - Inline table implementations
  - Repeated UI blocks (cards, stat widgets, list items)
  - Any logic beyond calling a server function or reading loader data
- Extract to `src/components/` when:
  - A JSX block exceeds ~50 lines
  - A block has its own local state (`useState`, `useReducer`)
  - A block is or could be reused across 2+ routes
  - A form, table, or dialog has its own submission/mutation logic
- Component naming:
  - Forms:   `<EntityForm />` → `src/components/entity-form.tsx`
  - Tables:  `<EntityTable />` → `src/components/entity-table.tsx`
  - Cards:   `<EntityCard />` → `src/components/entity-card.tsx`
  - Dialogs/Alerts that are NOT route-level: `src/components/entity-*-dialog.tsx`
- Pass only what the component needs — derive everything else inside the component
- Loader data is fetched in the route, passed as props to the component
- Server functions used by a component can live in the same component file if
  they are not needed anywhere else; otherwise extract to `src/lib/<entity>.ts`


# TanStack Table Rules
- All table code lives in `src/components/tables/`
- Two files per table entity:
  - `<entity>-cols.tsx`   — column definitions only (`ColumnDef[]` array + row type)
  - Reuse the shared `<DataTable>` from `src/components/tables/data-table.tsx`
- Never build a one-off table inline in a route or component — always use `<DataTable>`
- Never duplicate `DataTable` — if new table behaviour is needed (pagination, row
  selection, etc.) extend `data-table.tsx` with optional props, do not create a
  parallel implementation

## Row type
- Define a plain TypeScript type (e.g. `export type Client = { ... }`) at the top
  of the cols file — this is the shape of data passed to the table, NOT the raw
  Drizzle row type
- Map/transform Drizzle query results to this type in the route loader or server
  function before passing to `<DataTable>` — keep cols files free of query logic

## Column definitions (`<entity>-cols.tsx`)
- Export a single `columns` array: `export const columns: ColumnDef<EntityType>[]`
- Column file imports: `ColumnDef` from `@tanstack/react-table`, UI from `@/components/ui/*`,
  icons from `lucide-react`, routing from `@tanstack/react-router`
- Sortable columns: use a `<Button variant="ghost">` header with `column.toggleSorting()`
  and `<ArrowUpDown>` icon — wrap in `<div className="flex justify-center">` for
  centered columns
- Numeric/currency cells: always format with `Intl.NumberFormat` — never render raw
  numbers; use `'ru-RU'` locale and `'RUB'` currency for money values
- Badge cells: wrap count/status values in `<Badge>` with the appropriate variant:
  - `destructive` — risks, errors, blocked
  - `secondary`   — neutral counts (todos, upsell, etc.)
  - `default`     — active/in-progress status
  - `success`     — completed status
  - `warning`     — pending/not started status
- Array cells (e.g. managers list): render as `<div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">`
  with a `<Badge variant="secondary">` per item
- Actions column: always last, `id: 'actions'`, empty `header: ''`, right-aligned
  (`flex items-center justify-end gap-1`), use icon-only buttons:
  - View:   `<EyeIcon>` with `variant="ghost" size="icon-sm"` as `<Link to=".../$id/view">`
  - Edit:   `<EditIcon>` with `variant="ghost" size="icon-sm"` as `<Link to=".../$id/update">`
  - Delete: `<Trash2Icon>` with `variant="destructiveGhost" size="icon-sm"` as `<Link to=".../$id/delete">`
- Footer (aggregates): define `footer` on numeric/badge columns that benefit from
  totals; the first cell in the footer row always renders the label `'Итого'` —
  this is handled automatically by `DataTable`
- Zustand stores MAY be read inside `cell` renderers (e.g. `useDepartmentStore`)
  when column rendering depends on cross-route client state — this is acceptable

## DataTable component (`data-table.tsx`)
- Already supports: global search, per-column filters, sorting, footer aggregates
- Global filter already handles array-valued cells (searches inside arrays)
- Do not add client-side pagination unless the dataset is confirmed to be large
  (>500 rows) — loaders should filter/limit server-side in that case
- Do not add row selection unless a bulk-action feature is explicitly required

## Usage in route components
- Import both `columns` and `DataTable` in the component that renders the table
- Pass loader data (already mapped to the row type) directly:
  `<DataTable columns={columns} data={data} />`
- Filtering by Zustand store state (e.g. department) must be done BEFORE passing
  `data` to `<DataTable>` — derive `filteredData` in the component, not inside cols


# drizzle entities and types

When creating new entities always add raw DB types (Select / Insert / Update) in `db/types.ts`.

# domain / view types

Composed types that extend or pick from DB types (e.g. with extra fields like `role`, nested relations, or picked subsets) belong in `src/types.ts`. Do NOT put them in the store or in component files.

# server functions

- **Components** – all `createServerFn` calls live in `actions.server.ts` inside the component's feature folder (e.g. `src/components/accounts/actions.server.ts`). Plain async helper functions called only from within server handlers (e.g. `requireOwner`) also live there — no need to wrap them in `createServerFn`.
- **Routes** – all `createServerFn` calls live in a sibling `*.server.ts` file next to the route (e.g. `src/routes/transactions.server.ts`). If multiple child routes share a loader (e.g. `users.$id.ban.tsx`, `users.$id.delete.tsx`), extract it to a shared `users.$id.server.ts`.

# standard components rules

1. If adding Delete component, use `entityId` prop instead of `entity` prop, do not pass the whole entity object.

# drizzle entities and types

When creating new entities always add raw DB types (Select / Insert / Update) in `db/types.ts`.

# domain / view types

Composed types that extend or pick from DB types (e.g. with extra fields like `role`, nested relations, or picked subsets) belong in `src/types.ts`. Do NOT put them in the store or in component files.

# server functions

- All `createServerFn` calls live in `actions.ts` inside the corresponding component feature folder (e.g. `src/components/accounts/actions.ts`).
- Do not create or use `*.server.ts`, `actions.server.ts`, or route-level `action.ts` / `actions.ts` files.
- If a route needs server functions, move them into the matching component feature’s `actions.ts` and import them into the route.
- Plain async helper functions called only from within server handlers (e.g. `requireOwner`) also live in that same feature `actions.ts` file — no need to wrap them in `createServerFn`.


# file uploads

Use `<DocumentUploader>` from `src/components/ui/document-uploader.tsx` whenever an entity needs file attachments.

The component handles all upload UI state (selected file, uploading spinner, remove spinner, input reset). You only provide callbacks:

```tsx
<DocumentUploader
  documents={documents}           // { id, name, url }[]
  onUpload={async (file, base64) => {
    // 1. Call uploadDocument (from contracts/actions.ts or your own feature actions.ts)
    // 2. Link the document to the entity (e.g. addContractDocument)
    // 3. Return the DocumentItem so the uploader can add it to the list
    return doc
  }}
  onRemove={async (doc) => {
    // Unlink the document from the entity (e.g. removeContractDocument)
  }}
  accept={DOCUMENT_FILE_ACCEPT}   // optional, defaults to PDF/DOC/XLS/JPG/PNG
/>
```
